<subSubSection id="D405CD367D910968BCD55B0370848955" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="4FD283BDDB4AD95249D18CE1E23A4A9E" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">
<taxonomicName id="E67EA1E39EA53C4C3089E7FEDCBE3EF9" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amblycheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Amblycheila</taxonomicName>
Say, 1830a: 67. Type species: 
<taxonomicName id="8DFF1009EF47195AF8748092D371AEBE" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1823" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Manticora" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="cylindriformis">
<emphasis id="9457DB4E435FB1C8515514FECA05FEB3" italics="true" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">Manticora cylindriformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Say, 1823 by original designation. Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="D4B23932BD6A9F26FB19FC60D653CB42" italics="true" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">amblys</emphasis>
(blunt, obtuse) and 
<emphasis id="B1697E0B288EEB4D16B9FD6162FF6011" italics="true" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">cheila</emphasis>
(lip, by extension labrum [upper lip]), probably alluding to absence of teeth on the apical edge of the labrum of adults of this genus contrary to those of the genus 
<taxonomicName id="BDD9870CF93ED6ED64DFD096D4355761" authorityName="Linnaeus" authorityYear="1758" class="Hexapoda" family="Carabidae" genus="Cicindela" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="73BE70722824937B8CBF1D600BE545C1" italics="true" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">Cicindela</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
[feminine].
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DABBAAAE7B4C9E82F8B3B37320105A06" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">
<taxonomicName id="18BA13CB7E9C93C16B65701322507CA6" authorityName="Agassiz" authorityYear="1846" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amblychila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Amblychila</taxonomicName>
Agassiz, 1846: 16. Unjustified emendation of 
<taxonomicName id="79589EACDA63E50B9527EA15BE69F37F" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amblycheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="E600C3F260E6E2D9787FFDFC6653EBFE" italics="true" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">Amblycheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Say, 1830.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="25B0843AEC2A8206B772680391CE8973" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">
<taxonomicName id="12FCD80176E5901A377E294A3F3FF1E2" authorityName="Tilesius" authorityYear="1850" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amblyprosopa" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Amblyprosopa</taxonomicName>
Gistel, 1850: 75. Unnecessary replacement name for 
<taxonomicName id="B8861F7BCA48CCF42824AD5CDE69E25D" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amblycheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="FB7B8BB41F0FDC58268459EA0BA658E2" italics="true" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">Amblycheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Say, 1830.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="DE5A06AD2F7EC194527B1A12DF48B26E" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">
<taxonomicName id="629487D8A9EB6E4DD9E2BCF2E3EDDEF0" authorityName="de Chaudoir" authorityYear="1860" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Chaleposomus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">Chaleposomus</taxonomicName>
Chaudoir, 1861a: 337. Unnecessary replacement name for 
<taxonomicName id="C12359C07EEB3DD7390056236135D179" authorityName="Say" authorityYear="1830" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amblycheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis id="4D527E36BD296F7E555A61707D8B0FDB" italics="true" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">Amblycheila</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Say, 1830. Etymology. From the Greek 
<emphasis id="3A3F5A7F69047B2CBC148920D7C140AB" italics="true" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">chalepos</emphasis>
(difficult, severe, harsh) and 
<emphasis id="C1B94AD6ECD649E7C071625DDC70C6B3" italics="true" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">soma</emphasis>
(body) [masculine].
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="F59AEBDC7F63023A797975E593A30F44" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" type="diversity">
<paragraph id="3316DE00BB75216A80D1F2BDCD5240CA" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">Diversity.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="E4500F8EA5BCC0C5BF79A69B5922C42D" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">
Seven species (Pearson et al. 2006: 48) in western North America (five species) and northern Mexico (two species: 
<taxonomicName id="888FC532BD0EE941D7960AA47B253461" authorityName="Sumlin" authorityYear="1991" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amblycheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nyx">
<emphasis id="EF62A1E014C13B2D121A89E60C379681" italics="true" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">Amblycheila nyx</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Sumlin from west-central Coahuila and 
<taxonomicName id="A6A049EB69ECDB2453AD85447C1D47B8" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amblycheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="195" pageNumber="196" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halffteri">
<emphasis id="35E3428367FC0584A927B83E94AFABF1" italics="true" pageId="195" pageNumber="196">Amblycheila halffteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Mateu from San Luis 
<normalizedToken id="1726F9D507C29FC4C6FB943309221D01" originalValue="Potosí">Potosi</normalizedToken>
).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="1D39A34782F05B32C9F18FA43C6891D9" pageId="196" pageNumber="197" type="identification">
<paragraph id="8EC38E3DF32715622FF542F02F86245B" pageId="196" pageNumber="197">
<pageBreakToken id="471875E7B2485AB94F9DB3A43F83D87E" pageId="196" pageNumber="197" start="start">Identification</pageBreakToken>
.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="D50F1BA1682301BBBF4C459A794D6C55" pageId="196" pageNumber="197">
Vaurie (1955) reviewed the species and offered a key for their identification. Subsequently one new North American species, 
<taxonomicName id="0053BEC23FD075E57ABECCE0EC133A35" authorityName="Gage" authorityYear="1991" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amblycheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="hoversoni">
<emphasis id="3E8D03D3FA1BDCF1C33F0B0DC346A324" italics="true" pageId="196" pageNumber="197">Amblycheila hoversoni</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Gage, was described in 1991. Pearson et al. (2006: 22) field guide includes a key to the North American species.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="29C21EA2B79007F53A6E5808B034C91F" pageId="196" pageNumber="197" type="faunistic note">
<paragraph id="F9028B80E13C07800D5D7F45C75AC9C3" pageId="196" pageNumber="197">Faunistic Note.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="B8466CCD3CADBB6936943BA1848F916A" pageId="196" pageNumber="197">
The record of 
<taxonomicName id="76DE878F3743D3103E0669BF0033D5E3" class="Insecta" family="Carabidae" genus="Amblycheila" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Coleoptera" pageId="196" pageNumber="197" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="halffteri">
<emphasis id="41180F91C6DA8FE5354D79491697F9CA" italics="true" pageId="196" pageNumber="197">Amblycheila halffteri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<normalizedToken id="54B7A475FDAFA5D9E3033E4C46149E92" originalValue="“Texas”">&quot;Texas&quot;</normalizedToken>
(Bousquet and Larochelle 1993: 52) is in error. The species is known so far only from San Luis 
<normalizedToken id="EC4B47FEAB34313CD804B6C03DEA7EE3" originalValue="Potosí">Potosi</normalizedToken>
in Mexico.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
